wikipedia_page.main: Henry Kent Hughes (c. 1814 – 30 August 1880), usually referred to as "H. Kent Hughes", was a pastoralist and politician who sat in the South Australian House of Assembly from 1868 to 1875 representing the seats of Victoria and later, Port Adelaide.
